detail_description: The Blue Elephant Cooking School & Restaurant in Phuket is located in a beautifully restored Sino-Portuguese mansion that was once the residence of a prominent Chinese merchant. The restaurant offers signature dishes found at all Blue Elephant locations, as well as an impressive selection of Peranakan cuisine, thanks to a collaboration with a Peranakan association and Rajabhat Phuket University.

excerpt: Traditional dishes are served in this acclaimed restaurant set in a Colonial-style building.
detail_description: Nestled in a charming Colonial-style building, One Chun Cafe & Restaurant is a must-visit for anyone seeking authentic Phuketian and Southern Thai cuisine. This beloved eatery has garnered attention for its traditional dishes that evoke nostalgia with every bite. detail_description: Black Ginger is a modern Thai restaurant located at The Slate Resort in Phuket. Chef Anongrat Piak Meklai offers avant-garde Thai cuisine, featuring dishes like Moo Hong and Beef Massaman. detail_description: Acqua Restaurant, situated at the north end of Patong on Kalim Beach, is a top choice for those seeking an exquisite Italian dining experience in Phuket. detail_description: Jaras Restaurant is an upscale dining establishment located at The Intercontinental Phuket in Kamala Beach, Thailand. The restaurant prides itself on using only the freshest and top-quality ingredients to create delicious, well-balanced dishes that are beautifully presented. The menu offers a wide variety of steaks, including beef tenderloin and beef strip loin, as well as Kurobuta pork chops, grill-roasted chicken, and seafood items. address: Beach, 39/9 Muen-Ngern Rd, Tambon Patong, Amphoe Kathu, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Kan Eang at Pier is a renowned outdoor restaurant located at Chalong Bay in Phuket, Thailand. With almost 50 years of history, it offers a relaxing al-fresco dining experience with a focus on local seafood prepared in various styles. The menu features delicacies such as horseshoe crab, golden snapper, oysters, and rock lobster that are freshly caught and grilled over coconut-husk charcoals.

Chef Jim Ophorst's approach focuses on utilizing produce from Pru Jampa, an organic farm by Trisara, and obtaining proteins directly from local farmers and fishermen who follow sustainable practices. excerpt: Popular evening destination for classic street food in a utilitarian, open-air setting.

The restaurant has been serving locals and tourists for over 15 years, with a focus on affordability and quality. address: V9MM+V2W, Krabi, Tambon Talat Nuea, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Sam's Steaks and Grill in Patong, Phuket, stands out by focusing on succulent steaks and grilled meats rather than the area's typical seafood. name: Baan Rim Pa ... (Ban Rim Pha)

detail_description: L'Arôme by the Sea is a contemporary French restaurant located at Kalim Bay in Phuket. detail_description: Ta Khai, located within the Trisara Resort in Phuket, offers a charming and rustic dining experience with a focus on seafood made from fresh local ingredients. detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Phuket, Suay Restaurant is a culinary gem that captivates both locals and visitors alike. detail_description: Kopitiam by Wilai is a charming cafe located in Phuket Old Town, offering traditional kopi and a variety of snacks at affordable prices. detail_description: Nestled in the serene southern village of Nai Harn, Rock Salt Restaurant stands out as a hidden gem for those seeking an exceptional dining experience by the beach. detail_description: If you're in Phuket and craving authentic Thai cuisine, look no further than Natural Restaurant, also known as Tamachart Restaurant. detail_description: Rimpan Seafood is a hidden gem located in the north of Phuket Island, near the Sarasin bridge. address: 90/10 บ้านแหลม หิน หมู่ 7 ถนน เทพ กษัตรีย์ อำเภอ เมือง ภูเก็ต Thepkrasattri Rd, ตำบล เกาะแก้ว, Ko Kaeo, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Boathouse Restaurant in Cherngtalay offers a unique dining experience with a blend of traditional Thai dishes and international flavors. The restaurant's interior design provides an intimate ambiance with indoor and outdoor dining areas, a counter bar, and BBQ terrace.

detail_description: Red Sauce is an Italian restaurant located within the Rosewood Phuket hotel. The menu boasts an array of tangy and perfectly spiced dishes that are sure to tantalize your taste buds.

detail_description: La Gaetana is a charming Italian restaurant located in the heart of Phuket Town. The intimate setting, run by an Italian-Thai couple, exudes the atmosphere of a stylish trattoria with high-class yet laid-back vibes.
name: La Gaetana Restaurant
address: 352 Phuket Rd, Talat Yai, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

excerpt: Informal night market offering an array of meat & seafood alongside fruits, sweets & other wares.
detail_description: Chillva Market in Phuket is a trendy and vibrant night market that stands out among the others on the island. It attracts a younger crowd with its creative use of old shipping containers, creating a hip and modern atmosphere. The market offers an array of local food stalls, including meat, seafood, fruits, and sweets. In addition to the culinary delights, visitors can also find fashion items, authentic souvenirs, locally produced clothing and jewelry, athletic shoes, accessories, and gadgets.

excerpt: Luxury pavilions & villas in a posh beachfront resort offering 4 dining options & an infinity pool.
detail_description: Amanpuri is a luxurious beachfront resort in Phuket, Thailand, offering a range of accommodation including pavilions and villas with private pools. The hotel, established in 1988, boasts Lanna-style architecture and a serene setting overlooking the Andaman Sea. Guests can enjoy Japanese and Thai dining options, as well as access to a holistic wellness center. The resort features an infinity pool at the entrance and a dramatic staircase leading to the semi-private beach.

detail_description: Tunk-ka Cafe is a renowned hillside restaurant located on Khao Rang Hill in Phuket Old Town, offering stunning panoramic views of Phuket City. Divided into two terraces, the 6th floor exudes a classic big Asian city rooftop vibe while the 7th floor terrace resembles a top deck of a cruising ship with sunbeds and a small rooftop jacuzzi facing the ocean. The vast terrace features a circular bar, cozy sofas, and music by a DJ.
name: Kee Sky Lounge - Rooftop

With two kitchens serving both Thai and Bali-inspired Western dishes, this exotic oasis is a must-visit for those seeking an unforgettable gastronomic adventure. The atmosphere exudes tropical charm, making it a popular spot for capturing Instagram-worthy moments.
